Name: Nélson Semedo
Nationality: Portugal
Date of Birth: November 16, 1993
Position: Defender
Current club: Wolverhampton Wanderers
Premier League clubs played for: Wolverhampton Wanderers

Nélson Semedo, the Wolverhampton Wanderers defender, has played in the vast majority of the club's Premier League matches in 2024/2025, making 34 appearances overall and playing 2,895 minutes. He has been selected in the starting XI in 32 of these appearances across their 38 fixtures and come on as a substitute on two occasions.

Semedo last appeared in a league game on May 25, playing 90 minutes for Wolverhampton Wanderers versus Brentford in a 1-1 draw. This season he has provided four Premier League assists. He has been shown eight yellow cards.
In last season's Premier League, Semedo featured in 36 games for Wolverhampton Wanderers and created one assist.
Prior to joining Wolverhampton Wanderers in September 2020, Semedo made 82 league appearances in total at Barcelona, scoring two goals and providing two assists.

The defender debuted in a Premier League fixture for Wolverhampton Wanderers on September 27, 2020 as a starter against West Ham United aged 26 years and 315 days. Overall, in his Premier League career, he has appeared 165 times in the competition, with one goal and eight assists.
